<p>Modern California produces 85% of American wine across 600,000 acres, with innovative winemakers like <strong>Helen Turley</strong>, <strong>Randall Grahm</strong>, and <strong>Josh Jensen</strong> continuing to push boundaries while honoring terroir-driven winemaking principles that rival the world's finest wine regions.</p>

